The paper deals with graph drawing, which is a subfield of computational geometry (cs.CG). It also involves combinatorial aspects of graphs, such as chromatic number and treewidth, which fall under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem of drawing graphs with low visual complexity is related to graph theory (cs.GT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of lines and planes to cover the edges and vertices of graphs, which could be considered a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) or in signal processing and image analysis (cs.SI).
